comments.body:
[~ethomas]/[~tony]:

To clean things up, I retested this on [Group #2 cloud|https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/wiki/display/QA/Euca+4.1+Quality+Dashboard#Euca4.1QualityDashboard-Group#2] with two different templates; one with 'DeletionPolicy' set to 'Retain', and the other set to 'Delete'.  Verified that this worked just fine.

Eucalyptus version:   4.1.0-0.0.22963.319.20150109git45359c4.el6

*Steps*

# Applied IAM access policy to following group:
{code}
# cat cfn-euca10204-policy.json
{
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "Stmt1419017169361",
      "Action": [
        "cloudformation:CreateStack",
        "cloudformation:DescribeStacks",
        "cloudformation:GetTemplate",
        "cloudformation:DeleteStack",
        "cloudformation:DescribeStackEvents",
        "cloudformation:DescribeStackResource",
        "cloudformation:DescribeStackResources",
        "cloudformation:ValidateTemplate",
        "cloudformation:ListStacks"
      ],
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Resource": "*"
    },
    {
      "Sid": "Stmt1419265568046",
      "Action": [
        "s3:CreateBucket",
        "s3:DeleteBucket",
        "s3:DeleteBucketPolicy",
        "s3:GetBucketAcl",
        "s3:GetBucketPolicy",
        "s3:GetLifecycleConfiguration",
        "s3:ListAllMyBuckets",
        "s3:ListBucket",
        "s3:ListBucketVersions",
        "s3:PutBucketAcl",
        "s3:PutBucketPolicy",
        "s3:GetBucketTagging",
        "s3:PutBucketTagging",
        "s3:PutLifecycleConfiguration"
      ],
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}
{code}
# Created a cloudformation stack using the 'DeletionPolicy - Retain' resource attribute:
{code}
 cat cfn-osg-bucket-tagging-template.json
{
  "AWSTemplateFormatVersion" : "2010-09-09",

  "Description" : "Cloudformation Example => Create bucket with public-read access control list (ACL) and bucket tagging",

  "Resources" : {
    "S3Bucket" : {
      "Type" : "AWS::S3::Bucket",
      "Properties" : {
        "BucketName" : "buckettaggingtest",
        "Tags" : [ {"Key" : "Application", "Value" : "bucket-tagging-test" } ],
        "AccessControl" : "PublicRead"
      },
      "DeletionPolicy" : "Retain"
    }
  },

  "Outputs" : {
      "BucketName": {
          "Value": {
              "Ref": "S3Bucket"
          },
          "Description": "Name of OSG Bucket Created"
      }
  }
}

# euform-create-stack BucketTagging --template-file cfn-osg-bucket-tagging-template.json --region tessai-group2@group2
arn:aws:cloudformation::804704720152:stack/BucketTagging/e4d355ed-8835-48e0-ac29-0bc4749c4210
{code}
# Created a cloudformation stack using the 'DeletionPolicy - Delete' resource attribute:
{code}
# cat cfn-osg-bucket-tagging-deletion-template.json
{
  "AWSTemplateFormatVersion" : "2010-09-09",

  "Description" : "Cloudformation Example => Create bucket with public-read access control list (ACL) and bucket tagging",

  "Resources" : {
    "S3Bucket" : {
      "Type" : "AWS::S3::Bucket",
      "Properties" : {
        "Tags" : [ {"Key" : "Application", "Value" : "bucket-tagging-delete-test" } ],
        "AccessControl" : "PublicRead"
      },
      "DeletionPolicy" : "Delete"
    }
  },

  "Outputs" : {
      "BucketName": {
          "Value": {
              "Ref": "S3Bucket"
          },
          "Description": "Name of OSG Bucket Created"
      }
  }
}

# euform-create-stack BucketTaggingDeletion --template-file cfn-osg-bucket-tagging-deletion-template.json --region tessai-group2@group2
arn:aws:cloudformation::804704720152:stack/BucketTaggingDeletion/353662e0-9ef9-4dac-9c44-51742ad9eb29
{code}
# Confirmed stacks deployed successfully:
{code}
# euform-describe-stacks --region tessai-group2@group2
STACK	BucketTagging	CREATE_COMPLETE	Complete!	Cloudformation Example => Create bucket with public-read access control list (ACL) and bucket tagging	2015-01-10T02:15:09.752Z
OUTPUT	BucketName	buckettaggingtest
STACK	BucketTaggingDeletion	CREATE_COMPLETE	Complete!	Cloudformation Example => Create bucket with public-read access control list (ACL) and bucket tagging	2015-01-10T02:15:23.755Z
OUTPUT	BucketName	buckettaggingdeletion-s3bucket-qd2ndsqmfx28q
{code}
# Used s3cmd to confirm that buckets existed:
{code}
# ./s3cmd/s3cmd --config=.s3cfg-admin-hspencer-group2 ls
2015-01-10 02:15  s3://buckettaggingdeletion-s3bucket-qd2ndsqmfx28q
2015-01-10 02:15  s3://buckettaggingtest
2014-12-19 19:38  s3://ubuntu-vivid-server-amd64-19122014
{code}
# Deleted both stacks
{code}
# euform-delete-stack BucketTagging --region tessai-group2@group2

# euform-delete-stack BucketTaggingDeletion --region tessai-group2@group2
{code}
# Confirmed to see that stacks were deleted:
{code}
# euform-describe-stacks --region tessai-group2@group2
#
{code}
# Confirmed to see that the bucket associated to the template with 'DeletionPolicy - Delete' had been deleted, and the other bucket associated with the 'DeletionPolicy - Retain' template still existed:
{code}
# ./s3cmd/s3cmd --config=.s3cfg-admin-hspencer-group2 ls
2015-01-10 02:15  s3://buckettaggingtest
2014-12-19 19:38  s3://ubuntu-vivid-server-amd64-19122014
{code}

[~ethomas], I think this clears up the confusion.  Let me know if you have any questions.
